questDatabase.name: How to trade
questDatabase.description:
Build a Trader.
While the first recipes need no energy to run, the trade needs a little power to start up. For that place the battery into the middle slot in the inventory(invisible in GUI)

questDatabase.name: First Material Gathering
questDatabase.description: Everything needs to start somewhere. Collect some raw materials.

questDatabase.name: Starting in Void
questDatabase.description: Help Quest for Void Worlds (ToDo)

questDatabase.name: Road to Town A
questDatabase.description: To connect with Town A, a road is needed. The town is close and just a little bit more than a path should be fine, so it is cheap.

questDatabase.name: Road to Town B
questDatabase.description: A medium range strong enough for heavy transports. Should best be upgraded with rails soon.

questDatabase.name: Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Town B needs a lot of Electricity. Build Powerlines to supply them and make a lot of Money from them.

questDatabase.name: Animals
questDatabase.description: Even early on you need to keep some animals for meat and other raw materials. First make sure you can feed them.

questDatabase.name: New Homes
questDatabase.description: The homes in Town A are too few and too small. To build new homes the people need huge amounts of building materials. Supply them and become their usual trader.

questDatabase.name: Furniture
questDatabase.description: The people got new homes. But they are still empty. Supply them with some furniture and they might buy even more from you.

questDatabase.name: Melting Metals
questDatabase.description:
To melt down any kind of Metals, a Smeltery is needed. 
You also need lava and some molds, but you will be provided with your first ones. If you need more, take care of it yourself.

questDatabase.name: Automation
questDatabase.description: There is currently a sale for conveyors going on. They will safe you a lot of time, so best buy some.

questDatabase.name: Alloying
questDatabase.description: To start with GT Steam machines, you need Bronze. Make some of this alloy in the smeltery by mixing copper and tin.

questDatabase.name: Tools
questDatabase.description: For using GregTech you need many tools. Get a basic set of them.

questDatabase.name: More Tools
questDatabase.description: No Description

questDatabase.name: Basic Steam Machines
questDatabase.description:
The first tier of machines work with steam and are made of bronze. Build the basic set of them.
Early on the best supply is water from a water tank and buffering the steam in bigger tanks.
Not using steam that can no longer be stored will be wasted, on the other side, machines not getting enough steam supply will reset the production progress with an loud sound wasting all steam used in the process so far.
The machines can be stopped by hitting them with an mallet/soft hammer.
The square on the back is the used steam outlet and must not be blocked. Also, the steam hurts a lot. Both, while in pipes or when let out.
All sorts of plates can be used to cover GT machines, should that happen to you unwanted, you can remove them with an crowbar.
Last tip: The bronze boilers will autooutput steam on all sides besides the bottom. So best pipe in water from the bottom and take the steam from any other side. Wooden Pipes can NOT transfer steam!

questDatabase.name: Bronze Blast Furnace
questDatabase.description: The way to go for first steel.

questDatabase.name: Charcoal
questDatabase.description:
Start Producing Charcoal.
The Charcoal Pile Igniter is a early but fully manual way of producing charcoal.
To automate the charcoal production you need a Coke Oven, but that multiblock is slower and more expensive to build.
Much later on you can industrialy produce charcoal in the Pyrolyse Oven.

questDatabase.name: Automated Farming
questDatabase.description: Always caring about your farms is nice, but it certainly goes faster to automate them.

questDatabase.name: Medium Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines with better transformers and insulation for higher voltages. Even trough the loss is lower, huge power consumers usually pay less. As you can produce huge amounts of power quite cheap you usually still win when upgrading.

questDatabase.name: Low Voltage
questDatabase.description: Quests not ready after this point.

questDatabase.name: High Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to High Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Extreme Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to Extreme Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Bigger Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Bigger cables allow for more ampere to be transferred to cities so you can faster make more money.

questDatabase.name: Bigger Powerlines 2
questDatabase.description: Even bigger cables allow for even more amperage. But the costs rise exponentially.

questDatabase.name: Biggest powerlines in the town
questDatabase.description: Uprading the powerlines again is possible but extreme expensive. This has to be well tought trough.

questDatabase.name: Insane Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to Insane Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Ludicrous Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to Ludicrous Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Zero Point Module Voltage
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to ZPM Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Ultimate Voltage Powerlines
questDatabase.description: Upgrade your Powerlines to Ultimate Voltage.

questDatabase.name: Steel
questDatabase.description: Produce some steel. Now you can reach higher tech levels.

questDatabase.name: Water Collection
questDatabase.description: The world does not everywhere supply endless amounts of water. Only oceans and rivers supply enough water to be called endless. Everywhere else you have to find other ways. A early way for that is the Railcraft water tank or the forestry rain tank.

questDatabase.name: More Steam Machines
questDatabase.description: Some more Steam machines are needed to complete the full set and prepare for electric machines.

questDatabase.name: Circuit research project
questDatabase.description: A local team of researchers tries to optimize the production of circuits. Supply them with some research materials and they will reward you with some finished products.

questDatabase.name: Fluid Storage
questDatabase.description:
At the beginning water and steam, maybe lava. Later many more fluids. They need to be stored somewhere and best automaticly piped from machine to machine. A good early game tank for fluids is the railcraft multiblock tank.
This multiblock tank has automatic output on the bottom side and must be filled from top or the sides.

questDatabase.description: No Description

questDatabase.description: No Description

questDatabase.name: Logistics Pipes
questDatabase.description: No Description

questDatabase.name: Progressive Automation
questDatabase.description: Feeding, Milking and Shearing animals takes quite some time. Progressive Automation can take care of this job and more.

questDatabase.name: ProjectRed
questDatabase.description: ProjectRed  is the mod that supplies many tools to control your factory. Basic Logic and Timings come from here.

questDatabase.name: Bribes
questDatabase.description: It turns out it is really difficult to get Licences for trading in Town D. After some time it seems the only way to get in is to bribe some officials. Thats gonna be expensive.

questDatabase.name: Long distance connection
questDatabase.description: Town D is far away and a good new connection is needed. There is no way around building a railroad right from the start.

questDatabase.name: Branch Office
questDatabase.description: To be allowed to trade in Town D it is nessary to open a Branch office. After so many investments already this is just a small little step. Hopefully all this is worth it in the end.

questDatabase.name: Electronics Store
questDatabase.description: You gained permission to open a electronics store in Town D. Build it up and get the money coming.

questDatabase.name: Drugstore
questDatabase.description: Once people have money, next they want is health. And for that they will use lots of their money. It is difficult to produce them, but once you have set up the complex machines, you basicly print money.

questDatabase.name: Road to Town C
questDatabase.description: Building a Road to Town C is an important project. Your main supply of resources will come from here and so the road must also be durable. Asap this road should be also get a railroad next to it.

questDatabase.name: Tier 3 Materials
questDatabase.description: Once optaining Aluminium, your company got far enough to handle tier 3 materials.

questDatabase.name: High Pressure
questDatabase.description: High pressure machines from GregTech work faster than the bronze versions. The boilers are even recommended to build. The production machines are 50% faster, but use 100% more steam. So some prefer to wait with upgrading them until they get to the electric tier.

questDatabase.name: Better Trades
questDatabase.description: Better machines need better metals to be made of. Improve your trading connections with the nearby traders to get access to better raw materials.

questDatabase.name: Upgrading the power network
questDatabase.description: The powerlines connecting the houses in Town A are old and often fail. The pay is not as good it should be, but a growing town will buy more and more important, this is the basework to connect your own power station and start selling electricity.

questDatabase.name: Upgraded water system
questDatabase.description: There is a huge need to improve the piping system in Town A. Water supply is bad and the town grows fast. Expect good pay for this and likely more projects following.

questDatabase.name: Coal Mine
questDatabase.description: Coal is cheap an easy to get in huge amounts... and always needed. So best get early a trading licence for it.

questDatabase.name: Iron Ore
questDatabase.description: The most basic metal. Contained in many other ores, but best to get it as pure as possible.

questDatabase.name: Cassiterite Ore
questDatabase.description: Cassiterite is the ore containing tin. And tin is needed almost everywhere. Early on as alloy component in bronze, later for electronics.

questDatabase.name: Railway expansion
questDatabase.description: The amount of transferred ores now reaches a point where a railway is needed. A simple one will be enough for now.

questDatabase.name: Redstone
questDatabase.description:
Redstone, one of the mystery materials of this world. Used in electronics and for many other things.
The ore does also contain many other important byproducts. Rubys, rare earth metals and mercury to wash gold out of magnetite.

questDatabase.name: Copper Mine
questDatabase.description: Copper is one of the basic metals besides Iron and Tin. You just have to get this trading licence. You have to!

questDatabase.name: Bauxite
questDatabase.description: Bauxite ore is difficult to process, but the result is worth it. It is the main source of aluminium and with even better processing even some titanium can be made from it.

questDatabase.name: Opening a construction market
questDatabase.description: Always new factorys, expanding businesses, new products coming on the marked. There is always a need for building materials in this town. Also machines can surely be sold here for a lot of money.

questDatabase.name: Electric Hulls
questDatabase.description: First step towards electricy is making some machine hulls of the low voltage tier. These are needed for all LV machines.

questDatabase.name: Wrought Iron
questDatabase.description: The bronze blast furnace is really slow and expensive. So going quickly the half way might be better. A ImmEng Blast Furnace can produce Wrought Iron that is more durable than iron but not at the point of steel. You need it for electric machines and later on you can use it to produce steel more efficient.

questDatabase.name: Wires
questDatabase.description: Wires transfer electricity and are crafting components for many electric machines.

questDatabase.name: Magnetizing
questDatabase.description: The core of every motor comonent is an magnetic rod. For the LV Motors Magnetic Iron Rods are needed. These are made by combining an Iron Rod with 4 Redstone.

questDatabase.name: Casts
questDatabase.description: To make metal tools with Tinkers, casts are needed. To make Casts, you need gold or aluminumbrass. Gold is too expensive at this point, so best get some aluminumbrass.

questLines.name: Growing Company
questLines.description: Finally more Machines to help you.

questLines.name: Town A
questLines.description: A medium sized poor Town. They can't pay much but need a lot of food, building materials and furniture. Supply them good and they will grow. Maybe they will be worth it in the future.

questLines.name: Town B
questLines.description: A small growing industrial town. They need a lot of materials and energy. Maybe even machines. You can make a good business here. There is just the danger of growing competitors.

questLines.name: Town C
questLines.description: A medium sized mining town. Good connections with them will get you a lot of cheap metals and ores.

questLines.name: Town D
questLines.description: A huge and wealthy modern town. They have a lot of money and want to buy many luxury products. On the downside, it will be difficult to get started here.
